messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Explanation:
- In AdminController.newAdmin the method-level annotation is @RequestMapping(value = "/admin/register", method = RequestMethod.POST). That explicitly maps only POST requests to the path "/admin/register".
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so there is no additional prefix â€” the full path is exactly "/admin/register".
- Because the RequestMapping specifies RequestMethod.POST, only POST is accepted according to the source code. There is no declaration allowing all methods, nor mappings for HEAD/GET/PUT/DELETE/PATCH/OPTIONS/TRACE for this path in the shown file, so those methods are not acceptable based on the code.
